Closed date : 2017-01-30 08:11:46.29 Case Resolved Dear Constituent     The Boston Public Works Construction Inspection Unit (CIU) Inspector has identified that vault on the sidewalk needing attention as the responsibility of Eversource Electric.     Replacing or repairing vaults is not an easy repair.      Eversource has to have the vaults custom made for each separate location.      This takes time.  In addition the construction itself is technical and involved  as well as expensive.     We have informed Eversource Electric that they have to set aside resources to repair vaults around the City.    The estimated time for replacement is 6-9 months.      However  we will require Eversource to make a temporary repair such as the use of asphalt  especially if it is a major tripping hazard.     The temporary repair should be done within 3 business days.     For any questions or concern  please contact the number listed below    Sincerely     Mark Cardarelli  Supervisor of Utility Coordination and Compliance  Boston Public Works Department  617-635-4951 Office
